\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs79\f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid9846478 Unto the Lord in mine affliction have I cried, and He heard me.
\par 
\par O Lord, deliver my soul from unrighteous lips and from a crafty tongue.
\par 
\par What shall be given unto thee and what shall be added unto thee for thy crafty tongue? The arrows of the mighty one, sharpened with coals of the desert.
\par 
\par Woe is me, for my sojourning is prolonged; I have tented with the tentings of Kedar, my soul hath long been a sojourner.
\par 
\par With them that hate peace I was peaceable; when I spake unto them, they warred against me without a cause.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s91\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9846478 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9846478\charrsid9846478 Psalm 120.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9846478 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs79\f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid9846478 I have lifted up mine eyes to the mountains, from whence cometh my help.
\par 
\par My help cometh from the Lord, Who hath made heaven and the earth.
\par 
\par Give not thy foot unto moving, and may He not slumber that keepeth thee.
\par 
\par Behold, He shall not slumber nor shall He sleep, He that keepeth {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Israel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par 
\par The Lord shall keep thee; the Lord is thy shelter at thy right hand.
\par 
\par The sun shall not burn thee by day, nor the moon by night.
\par 
\par The Lord shall keep thee from all evil, the Lord shall guard thy soul.
\par 
\par The Lord shall keep thy coming in and thy going out, from henceforth and for evermore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s91\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9846478 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 Psalm 121.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9846478 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs79\f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid9846478 I was glad because of them that said unto me: Let us go into the house of the Lord.
\par 
\par Our feet have stood in thy courts, O Jerusalem.
\par 
\par {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jerusalem{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} is builded as a city which its dwellers share in concord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs79\f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid9846478 For there the tribes went up, the tribes of the Lord, as a testimony for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}
Israel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, to give thanks to the name of the Lord.
\par 
\par For there are set thrones unto judgement, thrones over the house of David.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs79\f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid9846478 Ask now for the things which are for the peace of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jerusalem{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, and for the prosperity of them that love thee.
\par 
\par Let peace be now in thy strength, and prosperity in thy palaces.
\par 
\par For the sake of my brethren and my neighbours, I spake peace concerning thee.
\par 
\par Because of the house of the Lord our God, I have sought good things for thee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid9846478\charrsid7173770 
